Project rules for autonomous AI agents:

1. Generate code only behind explicit contracts: services depend on repository-like objects, not concrete storage.
2. Keep storage in memory only. Do not add external databases, queues, cloud APIs, or network calls.
3. Use TDD for changes: every new branch of business logic needs unit or integration tests.
4. Preserve layered architecture: models contain state rules, services coordinate use cases, storage persists in memory.
5. Keep GoF patterns visible and purposeful. Current patterns are Strategy and Observer.
6. Do not bypass validation in models.
7. Maintain coverage at 70% or higher and keep SonarQube Quality Gate green.
